'''Lee Tae-seok''' ({{Korean|hangul=이태석}}; born 28 July 2002) is a South Korean [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|left back]] or [[Winger (association football)|left winger]] for [[FK Austria Wien|Austria Wien]] and the [[South Korea national football team|South Korea national team]]. He is the son of South Korean footballer [[Lee Eul-yong]].

== Club career ==
He joined FC Seoul in 2021.

He made his league debut on 7 April 2021, against [[Ulsan Hyundai FC|Ulsan Hyundai]].<ref>[https://sports.news.naver.com/news.nhn?oid=413&aid=0000116626 '이을용 아들' 이태석, 깜짝 데뷔전...가능성 보여준 '45분']</ref>

On August 1, 2024, he moved from Seoul to Pohang Steelers in a trade with [[Kang Hyeon-mu]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=조선일보 |date=2024-08-01 |title=[오피셜] 포항, FC서울과 트레이드 단행! 풀백 이태석 영입 → 강현무 서울로 이적 ([OFFICIAL] Pohang announces trade with FC Seoul! Fullback Lee Tae-seok to FC Seoul → Kang Hyeon-mu to Pohang) |url=https://www.chosun.com/sports/football/2024/08/01/557HWIYIFHZLO656NGRNKMW4PU/ |access-date=2025-03-26 |website=조선일보 |language=ko}}</ref>

== International career ==
He was part of the [[South Korea national under-17 football team|South Korea squad]] at the [[2019 FIFA U-17 World Cup]].

Lee made his debut for the senior [[South Korea national football team|South Korea national team]] on 14 November 2024 in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC third round|World Cup qualifier]] against Kuwait at the [[Jaber Al-Ahmad International Stadium]]. He substituted [[Lee Myung-jae]] in the 64th minute as South Korea won 3–1.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.com/football/match/_/gameId/710475|title=Kuwait v South Korea game report|date=14 November 2024}}</ref>

He made his first appearance for South Korea national team as a starter rather than a substitute on March 20, 2025, against [[Oman national football team|Oman]] in the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC third round|third Asian qualifying round]] of the [[2026 FIFA World Cup|North and Central American World Cup]] against Oman.<ref>{{Cite web |last=기자 |first=김아인 |date=2025-03-22 |title=[442.live] 'A-Match Starting Debut' Lee Tae-seok, “I got a call from my dad... Starter's chance? It's up to me to grab it” |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=69515 |access-date=2025-03-26 |website=포포투 |language=ko}}</ref>

He started at [[Defender (association football)|left fullback]] in a World Cup qualifier against [[Jordan national football team|Jordan]] on March 26 and played the full 90 minutes, putting in a strong defensive performance, winning five of his six [[Tackle (football move)|tackle]] attempts and winning all six ground ball contests.<ref>{{Cite web |title=South Korea vs Jordan - Lee Tae-Seok Match Statistics |url=https://www.fotmob.com/ko/matches/jordan-vs-south-korea/1j8bby?player=1107251#4523719:tab=lineup |access-date=2025-03-26 |website=FotMob |language=ko}}</ref>

Lee scored his first international goal on 18 November 2025 in a [[Exhibition game|friendly]] against [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]] at the [[Seoul World Cup Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Yonhap News Agency|url=https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20251118010651315|title=S. Korea squeeze past Ghana in final friendly of 2025|date=18 November 2025}}</ref>

== Style of play ==
Like his father, former soccer player [[Lee Eul-yong]], he has a precise and sharp left foot. He can play [[Winger (sports)|wing]] and left fullback, and his wide vision and left-footed kick allow him to deliver sharp long passes and [[Cross (association football)|crosses]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-04-23 |title='He's shining again!' Lee Tae-seok explodes for 3 straight assists... 'Golden left foot' just like his father, Lee Eun-yong |url=https://www.mhnse.com/news/articleView.html?idxno=270097 |access-date=2025-03-26 |website=MHN / 엠에이치앤 |language=ko}}</ref> Once considered a weakness, his defense and physicality have improved greatly in recent years, and in the national team game he shut down Jordanian winger [[Musa Al-Taamari|Al-Taamari]] to perfection.<ref>{{Cite web |last=기자 |first=김아인 |date=2025-03-26 |title='Jordan ace shut out→Hong Myung-bo praised' Lee Tae-seok, “I was honored to start for the second straight game” |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=69708 |access-date=2025-03-26 |website=포포투 |language=ko}}</ref>

